This is a snapshot of an anonymous checkout of the slicer2 cvs
repository checked out with these commands:

cvs -d :pserver:anonymous@cvs.spl.harvard.edu:/projects/cvs/slicer login

Enter 'bwhspl' as the password and then

cvs -z3 -d :pserver:anonymous@cvs.spl.harvard.edu:/projects/cvs/slicer checkout slicer2

3D Slicer version 2 is no longer actively developed, but is still available
for binary download at slicer.org.

A lot of training material is available, which serves as examples of what
is possible with the platform:

http://wiki.na-mic.org/Wiki/index.php/Slicer:Workshops:User_Training_101

Many of the 207 slicer-related publications at this site were
based on slicer2:

http://www.na-mic.org/publications/pages/display/?collection=11&entriesPerPage=50

